  "texts": [
    "However, its effectiveness is not without limitations, highlighting the complexity of benchmark design in capturing the multifarious nature of bias.",
    "The benchmark's broad scope sometimes overlooks the subtle, context-specific manifestations of bias, underscoring the need for benchmarks that adapt to evolving societal norms and technological advancements.",
    "Moreover, the dependency on predefined tasks may not fully encompass the dynamic and unpredictable ways in which bias can surface in real-world applications.",
    "The findings suggest a pressing need for continuous refinement of benchmarks, incorporating feedback loops from diverse user communities to ensure relevance and comprehensiveness.",
    "Furthermore, the integration of benchmarks focusing on underrepresented languages and cultures could significantly enhance our understanding of bias in global contexts."
